Male genitalia. Pygophore globose, distal half depressed; posterolateral angles slightly developed. Inner wall of genital cup swollen, projected dorso-posteriorly (
Fig. 9
). Lateral angles of ventral rim projected posteriorly; ventral rim carinate with an acute process medially (
Fig. 10
). Parameres quadrate, covering segment X basally. Surface of segment X concave, distal margin with deep U-shaped notch; each posterolateral angle of segment X produced posteriorly, acute apically.

Female genitalia. Genital plates glabrous. Gonocoxites 8 wider than long; flat; sutural margins parallel; lateral margins straight; posterior margins sinuate, somewhat reflexed (
Fig. 11
). Posterior margin of each laterotergite 8 with short, acute projection; laterotergites 8 each bearing a spiracle. Gonocoxites 9 swollen, strongly convex, higher than gonocoxites 8 . Laterotergites 9 swollen, acute apically, surpassing tergite VIII; laterotergites 9 tapering anteriorly; anterior angle of each laterotergite 9 attaining anterior margin of gonapophyses 9 . Segment X partially covered by gonocoxites 9 and laterotergites 9 . Gonapophyses 9 membranous; chitinellipsen elliptical; thickening of vaginal intima elongated (
Fig. 12
). Length of ductus receptaculli proximalis 1 / 3 of vesicular area; median duct of vesicular area sinuous basally; ductus receptaculli distalis as long as half-length of vesicular area; ductus receptaculli distalis convoluted distally. Capsula seminalis globose.
